HEADWORD: austenite
<hw>austenite</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Metallurgy)</fld> <ety>[From
<person>W. C. Roberts-<ex>Austen</ex></person>, an English
metallurgist.]</ety> <def>a solid solution of ferric carbide or carbon
in iron; -- it cools to form pearlite or martensite.</def>⟦br⟧
